<font color="#FF0000">GENERAL COMMENT</font><br>
<tt>Mon Sep 24 13:07:29 US/Eastern 2001
</tt><p>
 The things that I read on this site continue to reaffirm my belief that each of has dealt with our memories and actions in our own way. Some need others to talk to and some do not, but all need to talk about it even if just with themselves. I gain some insight each time I visit this site, but this is the first that I left anything behind. One of the ways that I am 'dealing' is I have started a collection of stories, perceptions, thoughts and comments about our experiences. I am particularily interested in the perceptions of young people and how they see the war. How have their thoughts been affected by vets they have met or stories they have heard, how do they feel when they see The Wall or read about the history of the war. I have, in my mind that I will someday publish this collection so that those to come will have a REAL understanding, not just historical knowledge. If any of you, or anyone you know would like to contribute, please contact me at edavis1@twcny.rr.com. Lastly, I would like to thank you all for your words, they help, each in their own way.
<p><code>-- edavis1@twcny.rr.com  (Ed Davis Jr) </code><p>


